  "original_lang": "ta",
  "original_title": "\u0baa\u0bb7\u0bbf\u0bb2\u0bcd \u0bb0\u0bbe\u0b9c\u0baa\u0b95\u0bcd\u0bb7 \u0b85\u0bb0\u0b9a\u0bc8 \u0b87\u0baf\u0b95\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bc1\u0b95\u0bbf\u0bb1\u0bbe\u0bb0\u0bcd : \u0baa\u0bbf\u0bb0\u0ba4\u0bae\u0bb0\u0bcd \u0bb0\u0ba3\u0bbf\u0bb2\u0bbf\u0ba9\u0bcd \u0baa\u0ba4\u0bb5\u0bbf\u0b95\u0bcd \u0b95\u0bbe\u0bb2\u0bae\u0bcd \u0ba8\u0bbf\u0b9a\u0bcd\u0b9a\u0baf\u0bae\u0bb1\u0bcd\u0bb1\u0ba4\u0bc1 - \u0bb5\u0bc0\u0bb0\u0b9a\u0bc1\u0bae\u0ba9 \u0bb5\u0bc0\u0bb0\u0b9a\u0bbf\u0b99\u0bcd\u0b95",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Bashil Rajapaksa runs government: Prime Minister Ranil's tenure uncertain - Weerasumana Weerasinghe",
      "author": "Vishnu",
      "body_lines": [
        "Former minister Bashil Rajapaksa is the main driving force behind the government. The tenure of Prime Minister Ranil Wickremesinghe is uncertain.",
        "Deal politics will never solve the current problems. Weerasumana Weerasinghe, Deputy Chairman of the Communist Party of Sri Lanka said.",
        "There is no doubt that former finance minister Bashil Rajapaksa should be held accountable for the economic crisis.",
        "Bashil Rajapaksa's wrong economic policy has destroyed the entire country. Bashil Rajapaksa resigned as a member of Parliament following the people's hatred.",
        "Bashil Rajapaksa is the driving force of the government even though he has resigned as a member of parliament. His intervention in the issue of gas and fuel purchase has been revealed through various factors. He is trying to achieve a narrow political objective by intensifying the crisis.",
        "It is worth noting that Investment Promotion Minister Thammika Perera has mentioned that Prime Minister Ranil Wickremesinghe should resign from the post of Finance Minister.",
        "Most of the members of Podujana Peramuna continue to express strong opposition to the President for the appointment of United National Party leader Ranil Wickremesinghe as Prime Minister.",
        "Fearing that his position would be affected if an all-party government was formed, the President appointed Ranil Wickremesinghe as Prime Minister.",
        "Deal politics can never solve the current crisis. Political stability must be maintained if the economic crisis is to be solved.",
        "He said, therefore, we emphasize that all political parties should pay attention to the establishment of an all-party government."
      ],
